    • patchDomesticatedDog

      public String patchDomesticatedDog(Long domesticatedDogId, DomesticatedDogPatchDto domesticatedDogPatchDto)
      A method (PATCH) will only update an existing object, with the properties mapped in the request body (that are not null). We do NOT update veterinarian appointment and medical data here.
      Parameters:
      domesticatedDogId - ID of the domesticated dog for which an update is requested
      domesticatedDogPatchDto - Data Transfer Objects that carries data between processes in order to reduce the number of methods calls
      Returns:
      a message stating that the domesticated dog is successfully updated, plus an optional String warning based on the weight of the domesticated dog
      Throws:
      EnumValueNotFoundException - throws an exception when the provided enum value is not found in enum
      RecordNotFoundException - throws an exception when domesticated dog / dog owner is not found based on ID
